subsection.p:
  Let's summarize the results. 

				\amp\text{Components: } 
					v_x = - y\, \omega,\ \ v_y = - x\, \omega,
				\amp\text{Magnitude, i.e., Speed: } 
					v = R |\omega|,
				\amp\text{Direction for counterclockwise motion: } 
					\theta_v = \theta + \dfrac{\pi}{2},

			where  \theta  is the angle on the circle modulu  2\pi and  \theta_v is angle with respect to the  x  axis. After we find the value of  \theta_v, we need to interpret the value for the direction based on the quadrant to which point  (v_x, v_y) belongs.
